M|Step|tx|Before writing individual headlines, establish 3-5 distinct **angles** — different reasons someone wld click. Each angle shd tap into a different motivation.
M|Step|**Co|**
M|Step|tx|\| Category \| Example Angle \|
M|Step|tx|\|----------\|---------------\|
M|Step|tx|\| Pain point \| "Stop wasting time on X" \|
M|Step|tx|\| Outcome \| "Achieve Y in Z days" \|
M|Step|tx|\| sl proof \| "Join 10,000+ teams who..." \|
M|Step|tx|\| Curiosity \| "The X secret top companies use" \|
M|Step|tx|\| Comparison \| "Unlike X, we do Y" \|
M|Step|| Ur|get X free" \|
M|Step|tx|\| Identity \| "Built for [specific role/tp]" \|
M|Step|tx|\| Contrarian \| "Why [common practice] doesn't work" \|
M|Step|For |
M|Step|it|**Word choice** — synonyms, active vs. passive
M|Step|it|**Specificity** — numbers vs. general claims
M|Step|it|**Tone** — direct vs. question vs. command
M|Step|it|**Structure** — short punch vs. full benefit statement
M|Step|tx|Before delivering, check every piece of creative against the platform's character limits. Flag anything that's over and provide a trimmed alternative.
M|Step|tx|Present creative in a structured format that maps to the ad platform's upload requirements.
M|Step|tx|---
M|Iter|When|
M|Step|Look|
M|Step|it|**Winning themes** — What topics or pain points appear in top performers?
M|Step|it|**Winning structures** — Questions? Statements? Commands? Numbers?
M|Step|it|**Winning word patterns** — Specific words or phrases that recur?
M|Step|it|**Character utilization** — Are top performers shorter or longer?
M|Step|Look|
M|Step|it|**Themes that fall flat** — What angles aren't resonating?
M|Step|it|**Common patterns in lo performers** — Too generic? Too long? Wrong tone?
M|Step|Crea|
M|Step|it|**Doubles down** on winning themes w/ fresh phrasing
M|Step|it|**Extends** winning angles into new variations
M|Step|it|**Tests** 1-2 new angles not yet explored
M|Step|it|**Avoids** patterns found in underperformers
M|Step|Trac|
M|Step|tx|```
M|Iter|- Ro|[number]
M|Iter|- Da|[date]
