M|Batc|For |
M|1. B|it|**hl generation** — Focused on click-through
M|1. B|it|**Description generation** — Focused on conversion
M|1. B|it|**Primary text generation** — Focused on engagement (Meta/LinkedIn)
M|2. G|- Wa|Core angles (3-5 angles, 5 variations each)
M|2. G|- Wa|Extended variations on top 2 angles
M|2. G|- Wa|Wild card angles (contrarian, emotional, specific)
M|3. Q|it|Remove anything over character limit
M|3. Q|it|Remove duplicates or near-duplicates
M|3. Q|it|Flag anything that might violate platform policies
M|3. Q|it|Ensure hl/description combinations make sense together
M|3. Q|tx|---
M|Comm|it|**Writing headlines that only work together** — RSA headlines get combined randomly
M|Comm|it|**Ignoring character limits** — Platforms truncate w/o wn
M|Comm|it|**All variations sound the same** — Vary angles, not just word choice
M|Comm|it|**No CTA headlines** — RSAs need action-oriented headlines to drive clicks; include at least 2-3
M|Comm|it|**Generic descriptions** — "Learn more abt our solution" wastes the slot
M|Comm|it|**Iterating w/o data** — Gut feelings are less reliable than metrics
M|Comm|it|**Testing too many things at once** — Change one variable per tst cycle
M|Comm|it|**Retiring creative too early** — Allow 1,000+ impressions before judging
M|Comm|tx|---
